@Comment:	MOT and Chi seem to get along , but they do not play together at all. Chi asks about three times during the activity if they are done yet. EXP stays in the background. Mot and Chi work independently for the most part throughout the activity. Mot tries to introduce the qualities of magnets to Chi a few times , for example by showing Chi how the balls repel each other , but Chi is not interested. There is some brief talk about how the thin refrigerator-type magnets aren't strong , that they <don't have enough magnet in them>. Chi does ask if everything is a magnet , but there isn't much discussion around this. MOT and Chi sit on a couch; the magnets and other toys (turtle , lego pieces , etc.) are on a coffee table in front of them; Chi is removing objects from the black base
